ympics, Murray is expected to compete in the singles and the men's doubles.\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1067, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4197404567549156e-39, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is already an Olympic champion, having beaten Roger Federer in straight sets to win gold at London 2012.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roger Federer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\"}, {\"begin\": 1230, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9978503387967751, \"rank\": 0.0021479493233392964, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray successfully defended his title four years later in Rio, when he was Team GB's flag-bearer for the Games.\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4197404567549156e-39, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999982083864, \"rank\": 1.791614674950513e-08, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.7190148520698136, \"rank\": 0.3805106223042451, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics will be 37-year-old Murray's fifth Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1360, \"end\": 1374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1395, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4197404567549156e-39, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 may not bring up the same emotions from Murray as his Wimbledon farewell, when an interview conducted by Sue Barker - who had been there on court for his Wimbledon final defeat to Federer in 2012 and his victory over Novak Djokovic the following year - provided quite the send-off.\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998522071, \"rank\": 1.477712707093687e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1477, \"end\": 1483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4197404567549156e-39, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1654, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two Wimbledon titles in 2013 and 2016  Two Olympic gold medals in 2012 and 2016  US Open champion 2013  Led Great Britain to Davis Cup title in 2015  Became world number one in 2016  He became the first British Wimbledon men's singles champion in 77 years when he won at the All England Club in 2013, before going on to win the tournament a second time in 2016.\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"score\": 0.935861658826044, \"rank\": 0.027464247762228403, \"text\": \"US Open\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davis_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9903433403184781, \"rank\": 0.008204136974923419, \"text\": \"Davis Cup\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davis_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davis_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9964915473714553, \"rank\": 0.003158293350165609, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 1995, \"end\": 2011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All_England_Lawn_Tennis_and_Croquet_Club\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"All England Club\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All_England_Lawn_Tennis_and_Croquet_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All_England_Lawn_Tennis_and_Croquet_Club\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then became the only man to win two Olympic gold medals in the singles at Rio in 2016.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2160, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999982083864, \"rank\": 1.791614674950513e-08, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His career was derailed by a chronic hip injury, and over the last few years he has struggled to achieve the level that saw him become world No 1 in 2016.\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He first announced his retirement atthe Australian Open in 2019, before returning after hip surgery.\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the start of 2024 he indicated that he planned to finish at some point over the summer but he had been vague as to the exact date.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ankle injury he suffered at the Miami Open in March cast doubt over his ability to even appear at Wimbledon, and another setback came when he sustained a back injury at Queen's Club and underwent an operation to remove a spinal cyst, which ultimately limited him to just one doubles appearance.\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray has always fought for others, correcting those who diminished the achievements of female tennis players, and will be remembered for being Britain's first men's singles Wimbledon champion since Fred Perry in 1936.\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 3086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2867, \"end\": 2873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4197404567549156e-39, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 3012, \"end\": 3019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9722583320629842, \"rank\": 0.028489656057212598, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3067, \"end\": 3077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Perry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5479216289539137e-45, \"text\": \"Fred Perry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Perry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Perry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First ministerJohn SwinneyhailedMurrayas \\\"our greatest ever sportsman\\\" as the tennis star announced his decision to retire from tennis after theParisOlympics.\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a post on X, the first minister thanked the 37-year-old for \\\"an outstanding and inspiring career which has made a profound impact on so many\\\".\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wimbledon posted: \\\"All the best, @andy_murray,\\\" and his mother Judy commented: \\\"5th Olympics.\", \"from\": 3395, \"to\": 3488, \"entities\